misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes trip cost can be computed by first finding gallons used as (distance ÷ milesPerGallon) and then multiplying by (pricePerGallon).
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: There is no gap here: this matches the intended notional model (fuel used = distance / fuel economy; cost = fuel used * price).
misconceptions.error_manifestation: No error; output is correct for the given inputs (modulo normal floating-point formatting/rounding).
